        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "docs: document coordinator deployment options",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- make the README and core docs describe the shared coordinator across Cloudflare and Node.js/PostgreSQL runtimes\n- add deployment guidance for containers, VMs, Kubernetes, TLS-verified PostgreSQL, ingress identity, shutdown, and single-replica operation\n- update provider, auth, security, portal, cleanup, telemetry, artifacts, and egress docs to remove Cloudflare-only assumptions\n- add Node typecheck, bundle build, and OCI image build to CI\n\n## Verification\n\n- `scripts/check-docs.sh`\n- `npm run format:check --prefix worker`\n- `npm run lint --prefix worker`\n- `npm run check:node --prefix worker`\n- `npm test --prefix worker` (412 tests)\n- `npm run build:node --prefix worker`\n- `docker build -f worker/Dockerfile.node -t crabbox-coordinator:docs-proof worker`\n- workflow YAML parse\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local --stream-engine-output` (clean)\n\n### Final-head proof\n\n- `scripts/check-docs.sh`: 47 command docs valid, 168 Markdown files linked, docs site built.\n- Node 24 Worker gates: format, lint, and Node typecheck passed.\n- `npm test --prefix worker`: 18 files and 412 tests passed.\n- Autoreview: no accepted or actionable findings; patch correct at 0.99 confidence.\n- CI on the prior content head passed Worker, Docs, Scripts, Apple VZ, CodeQL, and Socket checks; the final cleanup head is awaiting its fresh exact-head run.\n\n### Auth lifetime review note\n\nThe 180-day OAuth token documentation matches current behavior. `worker/src/oauth.ts` defaults `CRABBOX_USER_TOKEN_TTL_SECONDS` to `180 * 24 * 60 * 60` and passes that explicit `ttlSeconds` value into `issueUserToken`. The 30-day expression in `worker/src/auth.ts` is only the fallback for callers that omit `ttlSeconds`.\n\n## Operational notes\n\n- Cloudflare remains the established deployment.\n- Node/PostgreSQL is documented as an initial single-replica runtime requiring PostgreSQL 13+, verified database TLS for remote connections, and environment-specific proof before production cutover.\n- There is no automatic Durable Object to PostgreSQL state migration.\n",
